  "commitMessage" : "Limit stream upload length according to bodyContentLength specified (#3730)\n\n### Issue Link :link:\r\n<!-- What issue does this fix? If an issue doesn't exist, remove this\r\nsection. -->\r\n[Can't upload a specific length of\r\nMultipartFormData.BodyPart.bodyContentLength from an InputStream\r\n#3714](https://github.com/Alamofire/Alamofire/issues/3714)\r\n\r\n### Goals :soccer:\r\n<!-- List the high-level objectives of this pull request. -->\r\n<!-- Include any relevant context. -->\r\nLimit the writing of a MultipartFormData input stream to only the\r\nspecified content length,\r\n\r\n### Implementation Details :construction:\r\n<!-- Explain the reasoning behind any architectural changes. -->\r\n<!-- Highlight any new functionality. -->\r\nAdd `MultipartFormData.BodyPart.bodyContentLength` to constraint the\r\n`while` loop doing the writing.\r\n\r\n### Testing Details :mag:\r\n<!-- Describe what tests you've added for your changes. -->\r\nCreated test\r\n`MultipartFormDataWriteEncodedDataToDiskTestCase.testWritingEncodedStreamBodyPartToDiskRespectingBodyLength`.",
